// =============================================================================
// core/database/mod.vr — Spindle (Verum database client framework)
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 3 (Database)
// Spec: internal/specs/database.md
// Codename: spindle
// =============================================================================
//
// Spindle is the Verum database client framework. It provides:
//
//   * `core.database.common`  — vendor-neutral protocol surface
//                               (Adapter / Connection / Transaction /
//                                Row / Params / PreparedQuery / Pool /
//                                DbError / RetryPolicy / capability
//                                markers).
//
//   * `core.database.sqlite`  — pure-Verum SQLite implementation
//                               (loom: spec internal/specs/sqlite-native.md).
//
//   * `core.database.postgres` — pure-Verum Postgres v3 wire driver
//                               (alpha — see internal/specs/database.md
//                               §6.1 for the surface).
//
//   * `core.database.mysql`    — pure-Verum MySQL 8 binary driver
//                               (alpha — see internal/specs/database.md
//                               §6.3 for the surface).
//
// Cross-vendor portable code is the unusual case — handlers normally
// `mount core.database.postgres;` directly. The `common` module exists
// so a single retry combinator and a single `IntoResponse` bridge can
// cover all three back ends.
// =============================================================================

module core.database;

public module common;
public module sqlite;
public module postgres;
